[30;1m3 | [0m[35mContour finding[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35m===============[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mWe use a marching squares method to find constant valued contours in an image.[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mIn ``skimage.measure.find_contours``, array values are linearly interpolated[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35mto provide better precision of the output contours. Contours which intersect[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mthe image edge are open; all others are closed.[0m

[30;1m157 | [0m[35m# **Morphological thinning**[0m
[30;1m158 | [0m[35m#[0m
[30;1m159 | [0m[35m# Morphological thinning, implemented in the `thin` function, works on the[0m
[30;1m160 | [0m[35m# same principle as `skeletonize`: remove pixels from the borders at each[0m
[30;1m161 | [0m[35m# iteration until none can be removed without altering the connectivity. The[0m
[30;1m162 | [0m[35m# different rules of removal can speed up skeletonization and result in[0m
[30;1m163 | [0m[35m# different final skeletons.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m342[0m[34m of [0m[33m2067[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/scikit_image-0.25.2/doc/examples/edges/plot_skeleton.py[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m52 | [0m[35m#[0m
[30;1m53 | [0m[35m# ``skeletonize(..., method='lee')`` [Lee94]_ uses an octree data structure[0m
[30;1m54 | [0m[35m# to examine a 3x3x3 neighborhood of a pixel. The algorithm proceeds by[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m# iteratively sweeping over the image, and removing pixels at each iteration[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35m# until the image stops changing. Each iteration consists of two steps: first,[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35m# a list of candidates for removal is assembled; then pixels from this list[0m
[30;1m58 | [0m[35m# are rechecked sequentially, to better preserve connectivity of the image.[0m

[30;1m257 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m258 | [0m[35mrebase takes your changes (A, B, C) and replays them as if they had been made to[0m
[30;1m259 | [0m[35mthe current state of ``trunk``.  In other words, in this case, it takes the[0m
[30;1m260 | [0m[35mchanges represented by A, B, C and replays them on top of G. After the rebase,[0m
[30;1m261 | [0m[35myour history will look like this::[0m
[30;1m262 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m263 | [0m[35m                  A'--B'--C' cool-feature[0m

[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    C1-4 notation is taken.[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m    """[0m

[30;1m494 | [0m[35m    Given :math:`f`, a noisy image (input data),[0m
[30;1m495 | [0m[35m    total variation denoising (also known as total variation regularization)[0m

[30;1m286 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m287 | [0m[35m    Given :math:`f`, a noisy image (input data),[0m
[30;1m288 | [0m[35m    total variation denoising (also known as total variation regularization)[0m
[30;1m289 | [0m[35m    aims to find an image :math:`u` with less total variation than :math:`f`,[0m
[30;1m290 | [0m[35m    under the constraint that :math:`u` remain similar to :math:`f`.[0m
[30;1m291 | [0m[35m    This can be expressed by the Rudin--Osher--Fatemi (ROF) minimization[0m
[30;1m292 | [0m[35m    problem:[0m

[30;1m72 | [0m[35m    only needs to be swapped once when an element is removed. This means that[0m
[30;1m73 | [0m[35m    keeping an array of references along with the values is very inexpensive.[0m

[30;1m76 | [0m[35m    references, this implementation will probably be slower. If you need[0m
[30;1m77 | [0m[35m    references (and maybe cross references to be kept up to date) this[0m
[30;1m78 | [0m[35m    implementation will be faster.[0m

[30;1m159 | [0m[35m# To see what is going on, let's define a function, ``li_gradient``, that[0m
[30;1m160 | [0m[35m# replicates the inner loop of the Li method and returns the *change* from the[0m
[30;1m161 | [0m[35m# current threshold value to the next one. When this gradient is 0, we are at[0m

[30;1m10 | [0m[35mthe best threshold in most situations.[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35mUntil 1998, though, the way to find this threshold was by trying all possible[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35mthresholds and then choosing the one with the smallest cross-entropy. At that[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35mpoint, Li and Tam implemented a new, iterative method to more quickly find the[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35moptimum point by using the slope of the cross-entropy [2]_. This is the method[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35mimplemented in scikit-image's :func:`skimage.filters.threshold_li`.[0m

[30;1m157 | [0m[35mcoordinate conventions must match. Two-dimensional (2D) grayscale images[0m
[30;1m158 | [0m[35m(such as ``camera`` above) are indexed by rows and columns (abbreviated to[0m
[30;1m159 | [0m[35meither ``(row, col)`` or ``(r, c)``), with the lowest element ``(0, 0)``[0m
[30;1m160 | [0m[35mat the top-left corner. In various parts of the library, you will[0m
[30;1m161 | [0m[35malso see ``rr`` and ``cc`` refer to lists of row and column[0m
[30;1m162 | [0m[35mcoordinates. We distinguish this convention from ``(x, y)``, which commonly[0m
[30;1m163 | [0m[35mdenote standard Cartesian coordinates, where ``x`` is the horizontal coordinate,[0m

[30;1m550 | [0m[35mWriting a benchmark[0m
[30;1m551 | [0m[35m^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^[0m
[30;1m552 | [0m[35mTo write  benchmark, add a file in the ``benchmarks`` directory which contains a[0m
[30;1m553 | [0m[35ma class with one ``setup`` method and at least one method prefixed with ``time_``.[0m
[30;1m554 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m555 | [0m[35mThe ``time_`` method should only contain code you wish to benchmark.[0m
[30;1m556 | [0m[35mTherefore it is useful to move everything that prepares the benchmark scenario[0m

[30;1m10 | [0m[35mcorrespondences based on a weighted sum of squared differences of a small[0m

[30;1m13 | [0m[35m    The basic dilation operator, however, uses a footprint to[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35m    determine how far a value in the input image can spread. In contrast,[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35m    reconstruction uses two images: a "seed" image, which specifies the values[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35m    that spread, and a "mask" image, which gives the maximum allowed value at[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35m    each pixel. The mask image, like the footprint, limits the spread[0m
[30;1m18 | [0m[35m    of high-intensity values. Reconstruction by erosion is simply the inverse:[0m
[30;1m19 | [0m[35m    low-intensity values spread from the seed image and are limited by the mask[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35m    image, which represents the minimum allowed value.[0m

[30;1m6 | [0m[35mThe random walker algorithm [1]_  determines the segmentation of an image from[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35ma set of markers labeling several phases (2 or more). An anisotropic diffusion[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35mequation is solved with tracers initiated at the markers' position. The local[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mdiffusivity coefficient is greater if neighboring pixels have similar values,[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mso that diffusion is difficult across high gradients. The label of each unknown[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mpixel is attributed to the label of the known marker that has the highest[0m

[30;1m3 | [0m[35mThis module provides operators based on the max-tree representation of images.[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35mA grayscale image can be seen as a pile of nested sets, each of which is the[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35mresult of a threshold operation. These sets can be efficiently represented by[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mmax-trees, where the inclusion relation between connected components at[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mdifferent levels are represented by parent-child relationships.[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mThese representations allow efficient implementations of many algorithms, such[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mas attribute operators. Unlike morphological openings and closings, these[0m
